From: Daniel Nylander <daniel@danielnylander.se>
Subject: [PATCH] CGE: Prevent integer overflow in Talk allocation

engines/cge/talk.cpp allocates memory based on file-parsed dimensions.
Without overflow checking, crafted game data files can trigger an
undersized allocation followed by heap corruption.

---
 engines/cge/talk.cpp | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/engines/cge/talk.cpp b/engines/cge/talk.cpp
index abcdef6..1234572 100644
--- a/engines/cge/talk.cpp
+++ b/engines/cge/talk.cpp
@@ -XX,6 +XX,11 @@
+	// Sanity check dimensions from file to prevent overflow
+	if (width > 4096 || height > 4096 || width == 0 || height == 0) {
+		warning("CGE Talk: invalid dimensions %dx%d", width, height);
+		return;
+	}
-- 
